               <msContents>
                  <summary>A copy of Abū Bakr (Abū Ḥakīm) Rabīʻ ibn Aḥmad al-Akhavayn al-Bukhārī's
                     early medical encyclopaedia in Persian, Hidayat al-mutaʻallimīn fī al-ṭibb.
                     Akhavayn or Akhavaynī was a pupil of Muḥammad ibn Zakarīyyā al-Rāzī and wrote
                     this work in 183 chapters. This copy, dated 478/1085, is the oldest dated Persian manuscript in
                     the Bodleian Libraries and there is only one other copy extant - Istanbul
                     Fatih, 3646.</summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="MS_Pers_c_37-item1">
